  "text": "Alcoholic neuropathy is characterized by an axonal loss which predominantly affects small nerve fibers; in contrast, the axonal neuropathy due to thiamine deficiency has been reported to affect mainly large fibers [CITATION_1] . In chronic alcoholic neuropathy clusters of regenerating nerve fibers may be found in large numbers.",
